answers.q: what foods contain ethyl methyl cellulose
answers.a: E465 is commonly used in gluten-free and other baked goods, batters and coatings, sauces and salad dressings, and ice creams or other frozen desserts as a thickener, stabiliser, or emulsifier. On labels it may appear as E465, ethyl methyl cellulose, or ethylmethylcellulose.
